---
alwaysApply: true
---

- `packages/schema` owns the runtime scene shape, document format, validation,
  parsing, serialization, and migrations.
- `packages/core` owns scene helpers, command semantics, pure reducers,
  invariants, layout utilities, transform math, fixtures, and reducer tests.
- The scene graph is canonical scene state.
- Commands are the only mutation path for persistent scene changes.
- Keep reducers deterministic and side-effect free. No DOM, network, storage,
  clocks, or random IDs inside command application.
- Reducers must support replay, undo/redo, tests, and agent usage.
- Expected invalid user or agent commands must not throw; return unchanged scenes
  and structured errors through `applyCommandWithResult`.
- Replay-safe `DUPLICATE_NODE` commands must provide a deterministic `idMap`.
- Return the same scene reference for no-op commands where practical.
- Preserve graph invariants after every changing command: one root, no cycles,
  no orphans, valid child refs, one parent per non-root node, and valid
  selection.
- Store local transforms only. Compute world transforms from hierarchy when
  needed.
- Euler rotations are radians in storage. Three.js math is allowed in core only
  for TRS composition/decomposition that serves command semantics.
- Command contract changes must update `packages/core/src/commands.ts`,
  `packages/agent-interface/src/commandSchema.ts`, docs, and tests together.
